quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  19,16,And mention in the Book Maryam (Mary) as she retired from her family to an eastern place
  19,17,"So she took to herself a curtain apart from them; then We sent to her Our Spirit; (i.e., the Angle Jibril \"Gabriel) so he took for himself the likeness of a mortal in perfect shape (Or: mold)"
  19,18,"She said, \"Surely I take refuge in The All-Merciful from you, in case you are pious"
  19,19,"He said, \"Surely I am only a Messenger of your Lord to bestow upon you a most cleansed youth"
  19,20,"She said, \"However can I have a youth, and no mortal has touched me, neither have I been a prostitute"
  19,21,"He said, \"Thus (it will be). Your Lord has said, cSimple is it for Me, and that We may make him a sign for mankind and a mercy from Us, and it is a Command decreed"
  19,22,"So she conceived him, then she retired with him to a remote place"
  19,23,"Then the birthpangs made her come to the trunk of the palm-tree. She said, \"Oh, would I had died before this and become a thing forgotten, completely forgotten"
  19,24,"Then (one) called out to her from beneath her, \"Do not grieve. Your Lord has already made beneath you a rivulet"
  19,25,"And shake to you the trunk of the palm-tree (and) it will let fall ripe dates down on you, readily reaped"
  19,26,"So eat and drink and comfort your eye, yet in case you ever definitely see any mortal, (Literally: any of the mortals) then say, \"Surely I have vowed fasting to The All-Merciful, so I will never speak today to any human being"
  19,27,"Then she came up with him to her people carrying him. They said, \"O Maryam, (Mary) indeed you have readily come with a fabricated thing"
  19,28,"O sister of Harun, (Aaron) in no way was your father a woeful person, and in no way was your mother a prostitute"
  19,29,"So she pointed to him. They said, \"How shall we speak to one who is (still) in the cradle, a young boy"
  19,30,"He said, \"Surely I am the bondman of Allah. He has brought me the Book and made me a Prophet"
  19,31,"And He has made me blessed wherever I may be, and He has enjoined upon me prayer and Zakat (The poordues) as long as I am alive"
  19,32,"And ever benign to my (female) parent; (Literally: She who gave birt to me) and He has not made me arrogant, wretched"
  19,33,"And peace be upon me, the day I was born, and the day I die, and the day I am made to rise again alive"
  19,34,"That is Isa (Jesus) son of Maryam, in word of truth, concerning which they are wrangling"
  19,35,"In no way is it for Allah to take to Him a child. All Extolment be to Him! When He decrees a Command, then He only says to it, \"Be!\" and it is"
  19,36,"And surely Allah is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him. This is a straight Path"
  19,37,Yet the parties have differed among themselves; so woe to the ones who have disbelieved for the witnessing of a tremendous Day
  19,38,How well they will hear and behold the Day they come up to Us! But the unjust (ones) are today in evident error
  19,39,"And warn them of the Day of regret, as the Command is decreed, and they are in a state of heedlessness, and they do not believe"
  19,40,"Surely, We, Ever We, will inherit the earth and (all) who are upon it, and to Us they will be returned"